summary: FBI agents attempted to interview an unnamed individual at her New York residence regarding Jeffrey Epstein. The individual declined to speak without her attorney, Diarmuid White, and was served a grand jury subpoena to appear in Florida on June 3, 2008. She later called back seeking more information, and agents confirmed the matter related to Epstein.

keyFacts: An unnamed individual was served a federal grand jury subpoena in connection with the Jeffrey Epstein investigation in May 2008.
The individual initially refused to speak to FBI agents without her attorney, Diarmuid White, present.
The individual later called an FBI agent back seeking more information, at which point the agent confirmed the matter related to Epstein.
The subpoena required the individual to appear in West Palm Beach, Florida, on June 3, 2008.
The document is an FBI 302 form, indicating it is an official report of an investigative interview.
